   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>TRUTH LESSONS LEVEL ONE LESSON TWENTY-FOUR A KEY VIEW OF THE NEW TESTAMENT 8 THE NEW JERUSALEM OUTLINE The conclusion of the whole Bible and of the entire divine revelation: The conclusion of the whole Bible.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The conclusion of the entire divine revelation.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>God s work of the new creation in the old creation: Using the dispensation of the Patriarchs.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Using the dispensation of law.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Using the dispensation of grace.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Using the dispensation of righteousness.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God s work of restoration in the old creation: Using a short period of insertion.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Through His eternal gospel.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The results of God s work of the new creation and of restoration in the old creation: Producing the redeemed.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Obtaining the overcomers.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Constituting the New Jerusalem in the millennium.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Producing the priests in the millennium.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Producing the citizens in the millennium.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Perfecting the immature believers.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Purging to produce the people in the new heaven and new earth.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Terminating all the rebellious creatures of the old creation a secondary result.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Constituting the New Jerusalem in the new heaven and new earth.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The new heaven and new earth: The renewed new universe.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>With the new earth as the focus.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The New Jerusalem: Not a physical city.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The crystallized product and masterpiece of God s work of the new creation throughout the generations.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>A composition of the redeemed saints throughout the generations: The Old Testament saints.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>The New Testament believers.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>The bride of the Lamb.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>The tabernacle of God among men: The city proper being of pure gold.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The gates being of pearl.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>The wall and foundation being of precious stones: Jasper for the wall.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Precious stones for the foundation.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>The Triune God being the temple and the light of the city: The temple of the city.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>The light of the city.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>The throne of the Triune God being the center.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>The flow of the Triune God being the supply: Flowing in the middle of the street of pure gold.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>Becoming the river of water of life as the saturation.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>With the tree of life as the supply.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The mingling of the Triune God with the redeemed tripartite man.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>The kings in the holy city and the people around it: The kings in the holy city.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>The people around it.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>Conclusion.</S>
   </TEXT>
